  {
    "id": "UgxgEAvEz9wN0WhKhJ94AaABAg",
    "author": "@spex357",
    "author_channel_id": "UCFigH8Nyi-QLJksIo2tLjuQ",
    "text": "I've been using Photogrammetry for many years, for many things, a House, a Cliff, many monuments, Industrial machinery and plant. I have used a painters pole, a huge Carbon rod, and a selection of Kites to hoist my camera up for large items, and have even tried a drone on one of my local monuments. Lighting and focus are big influencers on the final result. Free apps have a limit on the number of photo's you can use, so you are limited  on size. Zephyr Photogrammetry is a good app.",
    "likes": 0,
    "published_at": "2023-10-26T19:30:18Z",
    "reply_count": 0,
    "replies": []
